text: The William McKinley Presidential Library and Museum is the presidential library to honor and remember President of the United States William McKinley. The library is owned and operated by the Stark County Historical Society. It is in Canton, Ohio. Canton is where McKinley built his career as lawyer, prosecuting attorney, congressman, governor and president. ==Other websites== * William McKinley Presidential Library and Museum McKinley Category:Buildings and structures in Ohio Category:William McKinley Category:Canton, Ohio
